PRETORIA – The Hawks were conducting a search and seizure operation at the Department of Rural Environment and Agricultural Development in Mahikeng in North West on Thursday morning. Formally known as the Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation, the Hawks said it was looking for documents still in the department's possession that pertain to an investigation that began in March. WATCH: Post cabinet briefing focuses on NW governance issues In March, the Hawks raided the office of then North West premier Supra Mahumapelo, who resigned on Wednesday. The unit said in March that the raid related to an investigation of fraud and corruption. African News Agency